com.dooapp.gaedo.finders.repository
Interface ServiceRepository

All Superinterfaces:
Map<Class<?>,FinderCrudService<?,?>>
All Known Implementing Classes:
InheriterRepository, SimpleServiceRepository
public interface ServiceRepository
extends Map<Class<?>,FinderCrudService<?,?>>

A service repository allows one to define which services are used for which bean and informer classes, and later to use these services to persist objects of the given classes. Notice the service repository can also be viewed as a Map of classes to associated services. Unfortunatly (well, unfortunatly, only for the most hackerish users) this is a read-only map.

Nicolas

get

FinderCrudService<?,Informer<?>> get(Type type)
Guess which service should be used for a given data. As an example, when facing a Collection type, it will check if inner data is typed. If so, it will use inner data type. This one method is a best guess method, able to provide *very* weird error results

Parameters:
type - any type
Returns:
maybe a service, if one can be found.
